During the final round of the Turf Machinery and Irrigation Limited sponsored event, Ciera bogeyed the second and third, picked up a birdie at the fourth, as well as ninth and an eagle at the 10th, though he bogeyed five holes in the process. Maara, who started with a poor round of 77 and 75 in the second round, made a tremendous recovery in the third round where he fired level par 71, though it was an improvement coming rather late as he managed to push Gathumbi to third place on countback 



